<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏗️ WD001 Week 1 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> HTML Basics — The Skeleton of a Page · <strong>Course:</strong> Web Design: CSS · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you build the <strong>skeleton</strong> of a web page with HTML. Every page is made of <strong>tags</strong>. Most tags come in pairs — an <strong>opening tag</strong> like <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> and a <strong>closing tag</strong> like <code>&lt;/p&gt;</code> — and your text goes in between.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each bit of HTML. Before you imagine the browser drawing it, write what you think will show up on the screen.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;h1&gt;My Pets&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have a cat named Coco.&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What appears on the page? Which line looks bigger, and why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;p&gt;I love pizza
&lt;p&gt;I love games
</code></pre>
<p><strong>These paragraphs are missing their closing <code>&lt;/p&gt;</code> tags. Do you think the browser still shows the text? What might look messy?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Welcome&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;img src=&quot;dog.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;my dog&quot;&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;This is my dog.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Describe in plain English what shows up, from top to bottom.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;h1&gt;Hello&lt;/h1&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong><code>&lt;img&gt;</code> does not need a closing tag, but <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> does. What do you think happens if you forget <code>&lt;/h1&gt;</code>? Write your guess, then test it later.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each bit of HTML below was meant to do something, but it is broken. Read what it is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, then rewrite it so it works. After that, explain why the original was wrong and why your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This is supposed to be one big heading that says <strong>About Me</strong>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;h1&gt;About Me&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the opening and closing tags should match.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — This is supposed to show a photo named <code>me.jpg</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;img scr=&quot;me.jpg&quot;&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> read the attribute name out loud, letter by letter.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — This is supposed to be a heading <strong>and then</strong> a paragraph. Right now everything ends up inside the heading.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;h1&gt;My Hobbies
I like drawing and coding.&lt;/h1&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the paragraph needs its own tags.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build Your About Me Page 📸</h2>
<p>Open Replit and start a new HTML project. Build an <strong>About Me</strong> page with these parts:</p>
<ol>
<li>a big heading with your name (<code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>),</li>
<li>a paragraph with <strong>3 things you like</strong> (<code>&lt;p&gt;</code>),</li>
<li>one photo of you or something you like (<code>&lt;img&gt;</code>).</li>
</ol>
<p>You can build it like this and change the words to be about you:</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;About Me&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Hi, I'm ___&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;I like ___, ___, and ___.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;img src=&quot;my-photo.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;my photo&quot;&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>When you finish, send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of your page (or a picture of your code), then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>First, I made the page with …</p>
<p>My <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> says …</p>
<p>The three things I put in my paragraph were …</p>
<p>I added a photo by …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you show your page. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never seen HTML. Try to use these words: <strong>tag</strong>, <strong>heading</strong>, <strong>paragraph</strong>, <strong>image</strong>, <strong>browser</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your finished page in the browser.</li>
<li>Point to your <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> and read it out loud.</li>
<li>Point to your <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> and say what is inside.</li>
<li>Show one tag you got wrong at first and how you fixed it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
